Package: geodetect
Type: Package
Title: Deep Learning for Geospatial Object Detection
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2025-04-25
Authors@R: 
    person("Lalit", "BC", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "lalitiaas@gmail.com")
Description: Provides a complete workflow for deep learning-based object detection
    on geospatial raster data (satellite imagery, aerial photographs, drone imagery).
    Implements a Faster R-CNN architecture with a ResNet-50 + FPN backbone via the
    'torch' package — no Python installation required. Handles the full pipeline:
    reading geospatially-referenced rasters with 'terra', generating image chips
    with overlap, assembling annotated datasets from bounding-box labels stored as
    'sf' vector objects, training detection models, running sliding-window inference
    on large rasters, back-projecting detected bounding boxes to geographic
    coordinates, and exporting results as 'sf' objects for downstream GIS analysis.
    Designed for ecologists, urban planners, agricultural scientists, and disaster
    response analysts who work in R and need to detect discrete objects (buildings,
    vehicles, trees, flooded areas) in imagery without switching to Python.
